STATE EX REL. KUDLA
v.
SUMMIT CTY. CLERK OF COURTS 2018-1663 Supreme Court of Ohio. February 13, 2019

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

O'Connor, C.J., and Kennedy, French, Fischer, DeWine, Donnelly, and Stewart, JJ., concur.

MERIT DECISIONS WITHOUT OPINIONS

In Mandamus. On motion to dismiss of respondent Ninth District Court of Appeals, and amended motion for judgment on pleadings of respondent Summit County Clerk of Courts. Motions granted. Cause dismissed.

Relator's motion for preliminary injunction with ex parte order denied as moot.
